## Hints for Future Agents
- `room_messages` has NO `round_id` column. Bucketing chat by round
  requires querying the round's `[started_at, ended_at]` window. Added
  `started_at` to the rounds select so this works.
- `guesses` has unique(round_id, player_id) so per-round-per-player
  total_score = the guess row's total_score — no group-by needed.
- Artist-mode safe: artist doesn't appear in `guesses`, so they don't
  skew the round average or compete for the swing pick.

## Codebase Discoveries
- The recap page is service-role-read-gated on `phase === 'game_over'`.
  Anything you add for in-progress games has to render the friendly
  "still in progress" state without leaking prompts.

